{"author":{"id":"8e1777f58c0cfe5478428be8f9fcbfe90d25e44689578335da8fc2246fe0915a"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1629792984,"nonce":"3Nxs10wnjHCqXrf27Xs3lI4LObI=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s416HC4","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/3896#issuecomment-904425656"},"message":"Afaik blast does not yet have a data manager. So admins do need to populate/tweak the blast directories and DBs on their own.\n\nI don't think we should run the `prepdb` command as part of the tool if this writes to the blast directory. In many installations those directories are read-only.\n\nUsing `blastdb_p.loc` makes sense to me, iff we tell Galaxy admins to also create diamond indices in the blast directories, or if we create a blast data-manager and offer an option to create diamond indices as well in the same process/directory.\n\n@peterjc any feelings here?","files":null}]}